Temperatures are expected to soar above 100 degrees in multiple states including California, Oregon, Utah and Arizona. "The heatwave won't go away." Officials say the extended heatwave, which coincides with a record-setting drought, has already killed at least 116 people in Oregon alone. According to a study by a group of climate scientists, the extremes in the Pacific Northwest would have been "virtually impossible" without human-caused climate change.Eight states recorded their hottest June on record, according to the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, and another six states logged their second hottest June.
